        {
          "plain_text": "Throughout my life, I thought that I wanted many things. Money, status, fame, women. The basic goals of most men; but as I slowly acquired them, the more meaningless life felt. When you don’t have anything, you’re sole purpose in life is aspiration, but what happens when you start acquiring everything you’ve ever wanted?",
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          },
          "href": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "texts": [
        {
          "plain_text": "I started realizing that many of things that I wanted were either from desperation or from outside influence. I realized that society, friends, and family were warping what I really wanted in life. What I really wanted was to be ",
